org.lunifera.runtime.utils.osgi.component.extender

Interface ContributionHandlerService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractComponentFactoryContributionHandler, AbstractComponentFactoryContributionHandlerPropertiesFile, AbstractComponentFactoryContributionHandlerPropertiesFilePerBundle, AbstractComponentFactoryContributionHandlerPropertiesFilePerItem, AbstractComponentFactoryContributionHandlerPropertiesFileResourcePerCategory, ComponentContributionHandlerPropertiesFilePerItemWithConfigAdmin

    public interface ContributionHandlerService
    A ContributionHandlerService is responsible to process the contribution resources coming from ContributorBundle components.

    The extender utility will bind to one registered ContributionHandlerService instance and will delegate to it the resource processing job whenever some bundle matching the extender manifest header is added, modified or removed from the container.

    A Contributor Bundle represents the 'extendee' bundle that is contributing something (using resource files) to other 'extendible' bundle through the 'extender' bundle.

    Since:
    0.0.1
